2014-12-18  Thien-Thi Nguyen  <ttn@gnuvola.org>

	[doc] Say simply "converter" instead of "type converter".

	The excruciatingly correct term would be "type-parameterized
	converter", but that's even worse.  We could also call it an
	"omm object", but that's weird, too.

	* doc/guile-pg.texi (converter): Omit "type" from expansion text.
	(Quick Start): Say "Scheme object" instead of "type".
	* doc/ref.texh (Octet Molding/Mashing): Update menu entries
	to say "Converters" instead of "Type Converters".
	(Consulting Existing Converters): Rename from
	"Consulting Existing Type Converters"; update text.
	(Builtin Converters): Update @cindex entry and text.
	(Defining New Converters): Rename from "Defining
	New Type Converters"; update @cindex entry.

2014-12-15  Thien-Thi Nguyen  <ttn@gnuvola.org>

